WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.000
<i>[This program is suitable
for viewers ages 15 and up.]</i>

2
00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:17.000
Subtitles by DramaFever

3
00:00:23.944 --> 00:00:25.051
<i>[Episode 6]</i>

4
00:00:25.051 --> 00:00:27.536
I don't have any anesthetics,
so I'll have to do this quickly.

5
00:00:27.536 --> 00:00:30.304
If you think this will be too much
for you, please turn around.

6
00:00:31.101 --> 00:00:32.795
I'll be fine.

7
00:00:40.454 --> 00:00:43.057
Have you ever given someone
stitches without anesthetics before?

8
00:00:43.057 --> 00:00:44.665
Of course.

9
00:00:45.484 --> 00:00:46.671
When?

10
00:00:46.671 --> 00:00:47.896
Or maybe I haven't.

11
00:00:52.730 --> 00:00:56.813
You should consider
yourself lucky, Ms. Soo Jin.

12
00:00:56.813 --> 00:00:59.599
My needlework is so good...

13
00:01:00.280 --> 00:01:02.719
that my nickname is Zipper.

14
00:01:03.617 --> 00:01:05.402
Give me just one minute.

15
00:01:06.046 --> 00:01:08.617
I'll make the stitches look
as neat as a zipped zipper.

16
00:01:09.882 --> 00:01:11.242
Oh yeah.

17
00:01:11.242 --> 00:01:13.237
Bite down on this.

18
00:01:13.947 --> 00:01:16.450
The stitches will come out
looking weird if you're too tense.

19
00:01:21.878 --> 00:01:24.114
Don't worry about me.

20
00:01:24.114 --> 00:01:26.462
Just pretend that I'm a bag.

21
00:01:26.462 --> 00:01:27.858
A leather bag.

22
00:01:36.727 --> 00:01:39.280
This is going to hurt a bit.

23
00:02:00.663 --> 00:02:02.292
Okay.

24
00:02:02.901 --> 00:02:04.801
You're doing great.

25
00:02:04.801 --> 00:02:06.717
Oh, you're doing great.

26
00:02:06.717 --> 00:02:08.259
How are you holding up so well?

27
00:02:19.372 --> 00:02:21.194
<i>Are you awake?</i>

28
00:02:21.194 --> 00:02:23.759
Can you tell me your name?

29
00:02:24.610 --> 00:02:26.328
What's your name?

30
00:02:26.995 --> 00:02:28.556
Kim Hye Na.

31
00:02:28.556 --> 00:02:30.481
What about your mom's name?

32
00:02:30.481 --> 00:02:32.736
Shin Ja Young.

33
00:02:34.781 --> 00:02:36.469
We're almost done.

34
00:02:36.469 --> 00:02:38.206
These are the finishing touches.

35
00:02:46.598 --> 00:02:50.048
I told you that
I'd stitch it up really nicely.

36
00:02:52.090 --> 00:02:54.919
Our breathing was totally in sync.

37
00:03:12.621 --> 00:03:14.609
Were you scared?

38
00:03:14.609 --> 00:03:17.858
I want to go home, Mom.

39
00:03:17.858 --> 00:03:21.914
You... want to go home?

40
00:03:24.073 --> 00:03:26.479
Our house.

41
00:03:26.479 --> 00:03:28.526
The barber shop.

42
00:03:30.080 --> 00:03:32.699
We have to sleep here tonight.

43
00:03:33.787 --> 00:03:34.963
What's the matter?

44
00:03:34.963 --> 00:03:39.520
Were you scared because the doctor
stitched up my hand with a needle?

45
00:03:43.431 --> 00:03:46.501
It's okay. It's okay.

46
00:03:52.764 --> 00:03:54.246
Is she sleeping?

47
00:03:55.026 --> 00:03:57.177
She just fell asleep.

48
00:04:00.492 --> 00:04:03.228
It seems like it hasn't been long
since you moved into this place.

49
00:04:03.228 --> 00:04:05.487
Well, it's been about two years now.

50
00:04:07.959 --> 00:04:11.535
I keep telling myself every month
that I need to unpack my things

51
00:04:11.535 --> 00:04:14.432
If I knew you'd be coming,
I would've cleaned up sooner.

52
00:04:17.649 --> 00:04:19.156
All right, now...

53
00:04:19.951 --> 00:04:23.156
I must ask you a couple of
questions, as a doctor.

54
00:04:24.526 --> 00:04:26.884
Are you being pursued
by a dangerous person?

55
00:04:31.103 --> 00:04:32.769
You mean this?

56
00:04:33.444 --> 00:04:37.596
When it comes to this,
I'm the dangerous person.

57
00:04:38.394 --> 00:04:40.999
Nobody did this to me.
I did it to myself.

58
00:04:43.704 --> 00:04:47.475
A woman refuses to go to the hospital
even though her hand is cut open.

59
00:04:48.060 --> 00:04:51.173
That woman didn't go to the hospital
when her child was ill, either.

60
00:04:51.173 --> 00:04:53.774
And I treated that child and that woman.

61
00:04:54.362 --> 00:04:56.454
As a doctor, I must know.

62
00:04:57.369 --> 00:04:59.447
What have I done?

63
00:05:08.257 --> 00:05:11.634
Did you have both of your parents around
when you were growing up?

64
00:05:11.634 --> 00:05:12.737
Yes.

65
00:05:12.737 --> 00:05:15.132
Both of your parents
were nice people, correct?

66
00:05:15.737 --> 00:05:17.127
More or less.

67
00:05:17.127 --> 00:05:19.708
Did you have a lot of friends
back when you were in school?

68
00:05:21.069 --> 00:05:22.521
I guess you could say that.

69
00:05:22.521 --> 00:05:24.483
Have you ever run away from home?

70
00:05:26.672 --> 00:05:28.319
Is this an interrogation?

71
00:05:28.319 --> 00:05:29.976
Did you eat well?

72
00:05:32.184 --> 00:05:36.755
Have you ever felt apologetic
toward someone every time you ate?

73
00:05:39.694 --> 00:05:43.630
Have you ever cried while dreaming
about sleeping in a comfortable bed?

74
00:05:47.300 --> 00:05:49.319
I was adopted.

75
00:05:51.413 --> 00:05:55.637
I was abandoned when I was six,
and was adopted when I was eight.

76
00:05:55.637 --> 00:05:58.511
And I barely have any memories
of my birth mother.

77
00:06:01.584 --> 00:06:04.384
I never once thought
that I wanted to meet her.

78
00:06:04.973 --> 00:06:07.704
Because I'm not that
woman's child, anyway.

79
00:06:09.451 --> 00:06:10.951
And...

80
00:06:12.257 --> 00:06:14.865
that woman is not my mother.

81
00:06:18.230 --> 00:06:22.284
<i>[Human Documentary - A Special Program
Featuring Actress Cha Young Shin]</i>

82
00:06:35.261 --> 00:06:36.757
<i>All children</i>

83
00:06:36.757 --> 00:06:39.343
<i>have a mother who gave birth to them.</i>

84
00:06:40.302 --> 00:06:42.004
<i>But...</i>

85
00:06:42.004 --> 00:06:47.617
<i>not all mothers can raise kids.</i>

86
00:06:47.617 --> 00:06:50.423
<i>The mom who gave birth to me</i>

87
00:06:50.423 --> 00:06:53.298
<i>couldn't raise me.</i>

88
00:06:53.298 --> 00:06:56.415
<i>So my current mother is raising me now.</i>

89
00:06:57.173 --> 00:06:58.836
<i>And that's because</i>

90
00:06:58.836 --> 00:07:02.401
<i>my current mother really needs me.</i>

91
00:07:05.504 --> 00:07:06.634
<i>[Human Documentary]</i>

92
00:07:06.634 --> 00:07:10.420
<i>Ms. Young Shin takes Soo Jin
with her everywhere she goes.</i>

93
00:07:10.420 --> 00:07:14.105
<i>She brings her to the set,
the hair salon, and shopping.</i>

94
00:07:14.105 --> 00:07:17.553
<i>Soo Jin will take
Ms. Young Shin's maiden name</i>

95
00:07:17.553 --> 00:07:19.411
<i>and grow up as Kang Soo Jin.</i>

96
00:07:19.411 --> 00:07:21.529
<i>Now, we will follow this
beautiful mother-daughter duo</i>

97
00:07:21.529 --> 00:07:24.867
<i>and set off with them together.</i>

98
00:07:24.867 --> 00:07:27.545
<i>I really need her.</i>

99
00:07:27.545 --> 00:07:30.387
<i>She needs to be around
for me to be able to focus</i>

100
00:07:30.387 --> 00:07:31.466
<i>and for me to be at ease.</i>

101
00:07:31.466 --> 00:07:33.434
<i>That's why the director
is extra mindful</i>

102
00:07:33.434 --> 00:07:37.146
<i>to make sure that Soo Jin
is comfortable on set.</i>

103
00:07:37.146 --> 00:07:41.144
<i>The one thing that I really,
really don't understand...</i>

104
00:07:42.387 --> 00:07:44.353
<i>something that baffles me so much</i>

105
00:07:44.353 --> 00:07:46.930
<i>that I wake up in the
middle of the night over it, is...</i>

106
00:07:48.242 --> 00:07:53.000
<i>what kind of mother...
could have abandoned a child like her?</i>

107
00:07:54.334 --> 00:07:56.721
<i>A child who is so precious...</i>

108
00:07:57.560 --> 00:07:59.319
<i>and special to someone else?</i>

109
00:08:03.855 --> 00:08:06.791
<i>She must have been poor.
She must have been unhappy.</i>

110
00:08:06.791 --> 00:08:09.237
<i>She must have had a reason
that she couldn't tell me about.</i>

111
00:08:09.834 --> 00:08:12.638
I couldn't shake off
these sorts of thoughts.

112
00:08:15.168 --> 00:08:18.274
Every time I put some
delicious food into my mouth...

113
00:08:18.924 --> 00:08:22.922
I thought that the person who'd
given birth to me was starving somewhere.

114
00:08:25.764 --> 00:08:27.451
I guess that...

115
00:08:28.196 --> 00:08:30.765
I pitied her.

116
00:08:32.054 --> 00:08:36.259
The person who tied up her own daughter
under a tree and ran away.

117
00:08:38.024 --> 00:08:39.514
But...

118
00:08:41.533 --> 00:08:43.868
I met her today.

119
00:08:45.748 --> 00:08:47.666
When I saw her in person...

120
00:08:52.596 --> 00:08:54.369
I felt hatred toward her.

121
00:08:57.403 --> 00:09:00.590
"How could you abandon your
own daughter and run away?"

122
00:09:05.640 --> 00:09:08.202
I wanted to scream that
at her and hit her.

123
00:09:09.094 --> 00:09:10.794
And so, I ran away.

124
00:09:16.625 --> 00:09:18.037
You did the right thing.

125
00:09:18.543 --> 00:09:20.538
That's completely normal.

126
00:09:21.490 --> 00:09:24.316
Your hand will heal up in a week.

127
00:09:24.316 --> 00:09:26.691
I think you were entitled
to do as you wanted.

128
00:09:28.378 --> 00:09:31.106
If it's not all out of your system,
though, go and wreak more havoc.

129
00:09:31.106 --> 00:09:35.013
You can hit her,
kick her, or yell at her.

130
00:09:36.907 --> 00:09:38.416
I will...

131
00:09:40.610 --> 00:09:42.174
never see her again.

132
00:09:42.174 --> 00:09:43.606
No.

133
00:09:44.700 --> 00:09:46.605
You definitely will see her again.

134
00:09:47.594 --> 00:09:50.900
You'll meander around,
then end up seeing her again.

135
00:09:50.900 --> 00:09:54.386
You'll meet with her and talk to her.
And you'll meet with her and cry.

136
00:09:55.277 --> 00:09:56.960
That's how people tend to be.

137
00:09:57.493 --> 00:09:59.658
That's the only way
you'll be able to get any closure.

138
00:10:09.923 --> 00:10:12.278
<i>I've never waited for you...</i>

139
00:10:12.856 --> 00:10:15.311
<i>and I've never once thought
that I wanted to meet you.</i>

140
00:10:17.320 --> 00:10:19.346
<i>I've never once thought
I wanted to show you</i>

141
00:10:19.346 --> 00:10:21.763
<i>what kind of person I am
or how I ended up living my life.</i>

142
00:10:21.763 --> 00:10:22.855
<i>Not even once.</i>

143
00:10:22.855 --> 00:10:24.336
<i>So, why?</i>

144
00:10:25.076 --> 00:10:27.849
Why did you run a barber shop here
for so long, at a place like this?

145
00:10:27.849 --> 00:10:30.615
All while being teased and
called a witch by the neighborhood kids?

146
00:10:30.615 --> 00:10:31.782
It pisses me off!

147
00:10:41.177 --> 00:10:42.503
<i>Mom.</i>

148
00:10:42.503 --> 00:10:44.028
<i>Why are you locking me up here?</i>

149
00:10:44.028 --> 00:10:46.325
<i>I'm not a bike.</i>

150
00:10:47.470 --> 00:10:52.096
<i>It's going to be a while
until I can come back.</i>

151
00:10:52.096 --> 00:10:56.326
<i>But it'll be bad if you go somewhere
and I can't find you.</i>

152
00:10:56.326 --> 00:10:58.601
<i>I'm not going to
go anywhere, though.</i>

153
00:10:58.601 --> 00:11:02.899
<i>I won't go anywhere,
and I'll wait right here!</i>

154
00:11:09.089 --> 00:11:11.139
<i>You promised me.</i>

155
00:11:11.998 --> 00:11:13.809
<i>That you'd come back
and unlock this for me.</i>

156
00:11:48.807 --> 00:11:51.342
<i>Yoon Bok! Yoon Bok!</i>

157
00:11:52.076 --> 00:11:54.504
Can you give this to your mom for me?

158
00:12:20.697 --> 00:12:25.401
<i>[Bank Account for Ms. Nam Soo Jin]</i>

159
00:13:09.206 --> 00:13:11.243
Hye Na...

160
00:13:11.852 --> 00:13:14.110
where are you?

161
00:13:17.730 --> 00:13:21.936
<i>The attorney told me that they
won't be able to indict me.</i>

162
00:13:21.936 --> 00:13:25.214
If they can't find Hye Na,
the fact that we abused her...

163
00:13:28.597 --> 00:13:31.687
Um, it's hard to prove
that those claims are true.

164
00:13:32.385 --> 00:13:34.432
And apparently, even if
this case goes to court...

165
00:13:35.077 --> 00:13:38.769
the worst sentence I'll get
is being on probation.

166
00:13:40.639 --> 00:13:43.013
Do you know someone named Kang Soo Jin?

167
00:13:43.013 --> 00:13:45.004
No. Who's that?

168
00:13:45.004 --> 00:13:47.225
Isn't she Hye Na's old homeroom teacher?

169
00:13:47.225 --> 00:13:49.514
No, I don't think that was her name.

170
00:13:52.470 --> 00:13:56.246
Go find out who Kang Soo Jin is.

171
00:13:57.346 --> 00:13:58.417
Why?

172
00:13:59.109 --> 00:14:00.847
If Hye Na is alive

173
00:14:00.847 --> 00:14:03.245
it won't be good for you.

174
00:14:23.147 --> 00:14:25.148
Did you sleep well, Yoon Bok?

175
00:14:25.687 --> 00:14:27.254
Where's my mom?

176
00:14:27.254 --> 00:14:29.644
She had an urgent matter to attend to,
so she went out.

177
00:14:29.644 --> 00:14:31.505
She'll be back before lunchtime.

178
00:14:31.505 --> 00:14:32.663
You're hungry, right?

179
00:14:32.663 --> 00:14:34.522
Let's eat breakfast. Come here.

180
00:14:35.648 --> 00:14:38.640
I'm not going to eat anything
before my mom gets here.

181
00:14:38.640 --> 00:14:39.787
Why not?

182
00:14:40.375 --> 00:14:42.820
This is super delicious, though.

183
00:14:43.360 --> 00:14:45.313
I guess I'll have to eat this
by myself, then.

184
00:14:45.988 --> 00:14:47.674
What is it?

185
00:14:48.746 --> 00:14:53.360
If you just pour hot water in this,
it becomes tomato spaghetti.

186
00:14:53.360 --> 00:14:54.755
It's my favorite.

187
00:14:54.755 --> 00:14:56.361
And this...

188
00:14:56.991 --> 00:15:01.975
becomes a hot serving of vegetable
bibimbap if you just pull this string.

189
00:15:01.975 --> 00:15:03.440
It's my second favorite thing.

190
00:15:04.695 --> 00:15:07.359
And these are black bean noodles.

191
00:15:07.359 --> 00:15:11.556
And this is a French military ration.

192
00:15:11.556 --> 00:15:13.799
If you heat it up,
it becomes chicken curry.

193
00:15:13.799 --> 00:15:16.226
Curry? I like curry.

194
00:15:16.226 --> 00:15:17.335
Really?

195
00:15:18.200 --> 00:15:21.039
I guess I'll eat the curry, then.

196
00:15:45.740 --> 00:15:47.140
Doctor.

197
00:15:47.140 --> 00:15:48.251
Yeah?

198
00:15:48.251 --> 00:15:50.267
We've met once before, right?

199
00:15:50.787 --> 00:15:51.821
Yeah.

200
00:15:52.706 --> 00:15:56.125
And back then, you asked me for
my name and my mom's name, right?

201
00:15:56.125 --> 00:15:57.361
Yeah.

202
00:15:58.498 --> 00:16:02.188
My name is Kim Yoon Bok.

203
00:16:02.188 --> 00:16:05.028
And my mom's name
is Kang Soo Jin.

204
00:16:05.678 --> 00:16:08.361
Don't try to find out
anything more about us.

205
00:16:08.361 --> 00:16:11.110
My mom isn't a bad person.

206
00:16:11.711 --> 00:16:14.650
My mom is the most precious
person to me in this world

207
00:16:14.650 --> 00:16:17.136
and I'm more thankful for her
than anything else in the world.

208
00:16:19.614 --> 00:16:20.907
Yoon Bok.

209
00:16:21.594 --> 00:16:23.347
What kind of doctor am I?

210
00:16:23.347 --> 00:16:24.783
A medical doctor.

211
00:16:24.783 --> 00:16:26.073
That's right.

212
00:16:26.716 --> 00:16:31.029
Doctors aren't allowed to tell anyone
what their patients tell them.

213
00:16:31.029 --> 00:16:33.070
That's the law.

214
00:16:33.070 --> 00:16:36.981
So, if I tell that secret
to anyone at all

215
00:16:36.981 --> 00:16:39.000
you can sue me, Yoon Bok.

216
00:16:39.000 --> 00:16:40.230
Really?

217
00:16:40.745 --> 00:16:42.508
What does it mean to sue someone?

218
00:16:43.717 --> 00:16:44.759
Oh.

219
00:16:44.759 --> 00:16:47.565
At any rate, everything we discuss...

220
00:16:48.200 --> 00:16:50.009
will forever be a secret.

221
00:16:50.009 --> 00:16:51.457
From Mom, too?

222
00:16:51.457 --> 00:16:53.027
From your mom, too.

223
00:16:55.895 --> 00:16:58.146
Do you think you'll be able to
have some breakfast now?

224
00:17:01.730 --> 00:17:04.308
Just because I'm eating this

225
00:17:04.308 --> 00:17:07.799
doesn't mean I'll tell you
anything about us.

226
00:17:07.799 --> 00:17:08.992
I know.

227
00:17:11.538 --> 00:17:15.885
I can't choose between
tomato spaghetti and chicken curry.

228
00:17:15.885 --> 00:17:18.669
At times like that,
you have to have both, right?

229
00:17:25.380 --> 00:17:27.653
<i>Ms. Kang Soo Jin?</i>

230
00:17:27.653 --> 00:17:30.741
There isn't anyone by that name
at our school.

231
00:17:30.741 --> 00:17:32.898
Oh, so there isn't?

232
00:17:32.898 --> 00:17:35.551
I see. Thank you.

233
00:17:37.661 --> 00:17:40.461
Honey, they said there isn't
a teacher by that name there.

234
00:17:42.609 --> 00:17:44.909
You know, the teacher
who came by before.

235
00:17:44.909 --> 00:17:46.689
The one who came to
the front of our house.

236
00:17:46.689 --> 00:17:49.180
You mean that annoying woman?

237
00:17:49.180 --> 00:17:52.082
No, the woman who came
with that teacher.

238
00:17:52.082 --> 00:17:53.438
Oh, was there someone else?

239
00:17:54.277 --> 00:17:56.787
Go see that annoying woman

240
00:17:56.787 --> 00:17:59.324
and ask her about Kang Soo Jin.

241
00:17:59.324 --> 00:18:00.801
Do I have to?

242
00:18:00.801 --> 00:18:01.951
Yeah.

243
00:18:21.846 --> 00:18:22.901
Student.

244
00:18:22.901 --> 00:18:25.263
Can you come back tomorrow?
We'll stop for today.

245
00:18:25.263 --> 00:18:26.405
What?

246
00:18:27.239 --> 00:18:29.757
I'll cut your hair
really nicely tomorrow.

247
00:18:31.193 --> 00:18:33.330
Big Bro.

248
00:18:33.330 --> 00:18:35.291
You have a big sister, right?

249
00:18:35.291 --> 00:18:37.557
I can cut women's hair, too.

250
00:18:37.557 --> 00:18:40.111
Bring her here tomorrow.
I'll cut hers for free.

251
00:18:57.376 --> 00:18:59.287
To be honest...

252
00:19:03.153 --> 00:19:04.936
I did wait for you.

253
00:19:07.411 --> 00:19:09.017
For quite a long time.

254
00:19:11.378 --> 00:19:13.913
But I worked so hard
for much longer than I waited...

255
00:19:15.500 --> 00:19:17.683
to get my head on straight

256
00:19:17.683 --> 00:19:20.714
and to stop waiting for you.

257
00:19:21.359 --> 00:19:23.538
I told myself that nobody
was coming to get me.

258
00:19:24.266 --> 00:19:26.623
And that that woman had abandoned me.

259
00:19:27.189 --> 00:19:28.846
That she wouldn't be coming back.

260
00:19:29.711 --> 00:19:33.817
I persuaded myself, consoled myself,
cried, got angry, and yelled at myself...

261
00:19:36.897 --> 00:19:38.752
while my childhood
passed before my eyes...

262
00:19:38.752 --> 00:19:40.970
and my youth passed me by.

263
00:19:41.828 --> 00:19:43.605
And now, I'm here.

264
00:19:51.499 --> 00:19:54.711
Did you think that I would
accept this, ma'am?

265
00:19:55.275 --> 00:19:57.022
Did you think that
I would thank you

266
00:19:57.022 --> 00:19:58.941
and be happy to see you

267
00:19:58.941 --> 00:20:01.710
and ask you if you've been
doing well all these years?

268
00:20:02.301 --> 00:20:04.641
If not, what are you doing here?

269
00:20:04.641 --> 00:20:07.989
If you abandoned me like that, the least
you could be doing is living a good life.

270
00:20:07.989 --> 00:20:10.665
Don't you think that's the very least
you could do for me?

271
00:20:17.532 --> 00:20:19.280
I saw you...

272
00:20:20.263 --> 00:20:21.808
on TV.

273
00:20:23.357 --> 00:20:25.726
It may have been different...

274
00:20:25.726 --> 00:20:27.946
if I hadn't seen who adopted you...

275
00:20:29.587 --> 00:20:31.769
and how you'd been living your life.

276
00:20:32.861 --> 00:20:34.728
But I did see you.

277
00:20:35.423 --> 00:20:36.717
I did.

278
00:20:44.479 --> 00:20:48.459
I was so sure that I could make sure
that you wouldn't find out.

279
00:20:48.959 --> 00:20:51.344
You'd never come to a
barber shop, since you're a girl.

280
00:20:51.344 --> 00:20:54.410
And it's not like I would've
confessed this fact to you myself.

281
00:20:56.167 --> 00:20:57.271
I just...

282
00:20:57.271 --> 00:21:01.019
wanted to see you go to school
and head back home every day.

283
00:21:02.517 --> 00:21:04.657
I just wanted to see you every day...

284
00:21:05.413 --> 00:21:06.759
and see that you were doing well.

285
00:21:08.327 --> 00:21:10.355
That was all.

286
00:21:13.461 --> 00:21:14.798
But...

287
00:21:16.459 --> 00:21:20.858
I had no idea that you'd appear before me
holding a little girl's hand...

288
00:21:21.932 --> 00:21:24.184
and that she'd come running here

289
00:21:24.184 --> 00:21:26.844
to the barber shop
in such frigid weather.

290
00:21:27.717 --> 00:21:29.777
I never would've expected it.

291
00:21:31.461 --> 00:21:32.963
I couldn't...

292
00:21:34.064 --> 00:21:36.358
just throw that away...

293
00:21:37.548 --> 00:21:39.695
but I couldn't use it, either.

294
00:21:41.303 --> 00:21:43.182
So I saved it up.

295
00:21:43.911 --> 00:21:46.075
That is a record...

296
00:21:46.727 --> 00:21:48.788
of how I've lived my life here...

297
00:21:50.392 --> 00:21:52.941
for the past 27 years.

298
00:21:54.943 --> 00:21:56.073
I thought...

299
00:21:57.003 --> 00:21:59.326
that you may need it.

300
00:21:59.326 --> 00:22:02.938
Even if I have to sell the clothes
on my back because I have no money...

301
00:22:03.878 --> 00:22:05.925
I will never accept
your money, ma'am.

302
00:22:06.452 --> 00:22:09.058
And don't say that you lived here
for all this time...

303
00:22:10.355 --> 00:22:12.173
because of me, either.

304
00:22:12.173 --> 00:22:14.500
Because I will refuse
to accept that, too.

305
00:22:25.852 --> 00:22:27.820
Let me ask you just one thing.

306
00:22:32.116 --> 00:22:33.903
Why did you do it?

307
00:22:39.363 --> 00:22:41.327
Did you hate me?

308
00:22:45.252 --> 00:22:47.807
Was your life difficult because of me?

309
00:22:56.854 --> 00:22:59.088
Was it that you were only
able to live your life...

310
00:23:01.031 --> 00:23:03.789
without me around?

311
00:23:12.041 --> 00:23:14.473
I don't remember.

312
00:23:16.596 --> 00:23:19.249
So I keep thinking about it
like a crazy person

313
00:23:19.249 --> 00:23:21.036
over and over.

314
00:23:28.597 --> 00:23:30.019
Tell me.

315
00:23:32.057 --> 00:23:35.567
This is the only thing that
you can do for me, ma'am.

316
00:23:38.116 --> 00:23:39.957
You can't tell me?

317
00:23:50.740 --> 00:23:53.428
I took back the money I gave you
for a month's worth of rent

318
00:23:53.428 --> 00:23:56.184
except the money I owe you
for the four days that we stayed here.

319
00:23:57.766 --> 00:24:00.248
Let's never see each other again.

320
00:24:19.820 --> 00:24:21.246
Thanks to you

321
00:24:21.246 --> 00:24:24.088
I managed to get a really thorough look
inside of a police station.

322
00:24:24.816 --> 00:24:29.227
It'd be good if you were cleared
of all charges, I suppose.

323
00:24:29.227 --> 00:24:32.823
So many people are working so hard
looking for Hye Na

324
00:24:32.823 --> 00:24:37.046
so I'm thinking about taking matters into
my own hands, and searching for Hye Na.

325
00:24:37.672 --> 00:24:39.986
Who's Ms. Kang Soo Jin?

326
00:24:41.234 --> 00:24:42.508
Why do you ask?

327
00:24:42.508 --> 00:24:45.897
You know, the teacher who came with you
when you visited my house last time...

328
00:24:45.897 --> 00:24:48.262
I forced her to come with me,
and dragged her along

329
00:24:48.262 --> 00:24:51.563
since Ms. Kang Soo Jin was
merely a substitute homeroom teacher.

330
00:24:51.563 --> 00:24:53.109
Oh.

331
00:24:53.876 --> 00:24:55.803
So Ms. Kang Soo Jin

332
00:24:55.803 --> 00:24:59.011
was Hye Na's substitute
homeroom teacher. I see.

333
00:25:00.106 --> 00:25:03.382
Yes, but she didn't stay
at our school for very long.

334
00:25:03.382 --> 00:25:06.277
And she had no interest
whatsoever in Hye Na.

335
00:25:06.888 --> 00:25:07.914
How do you know that?

336
00:25:07.914 --> 00:25:10.628
Because the person who was
interested in Hye Na was me.

337
00:25:10.628 --> 00:25:12.963
The one who was worried about her

338
00:25:12.963 --> 00:25:18.066
and the one who contacted the school,
police, and CPS again and again was me.

339
00:25:18.066 --> 00:25:21.172
She may have only been a substitute,
but she was still her homeroom teacher.

340
00:25:21.172 --> 00:25:24.599
Yet, she had no interest
whatsoever in the child.

341
00:25:25.602 --> 00:25:29.269
And she's not even in Korea now, anyway.

342
00:25:29.269 --> 00:25:30.880
Where did she go?

343
00:25:30.880 --> 00:25:32.327
Iceland.

344
00:25:34.919 --> 00:25:36.448
That far?

345
00:25:36.448 --> 00:25:39.584
She left before Hye Na went missing.

346
00:25:40.617 --> 00:25:43.207
She said that she
studied birds, or something.

347
00:25:44.202 --> 00:25:45.446
Oh.

348
00:25:46.390 --> 00:25:48.747
So she studies birds, you say.

349
00:25:56.191 --> 00:25:58.842
I'm heading out now because
I have an urgent matter to attend to.

350
00:25:58.842 --> 00:26:00.372
But I'll be back before dinnertime.

351
00:26:00.372 --> 00:26:01.683
Stay here until then.

352
00:26:01.683 --> 00:26:03.436
We have to go, too.

353
00:26:03.436 --> 00:26:05.773
We were planning to leave, anyway.

354
00:26:05.773 --> 00:26:08.340
Are you planning to go to
a hotel again with Yoon Bok?

355
00:26:08.340 --> 00:26:10.986
Yoon Bok is scared of being here.

356
00:26:10.986 --> 00:26:13.640
I'm going to try and find a place
to stay as soon as possible.

357
00:26:21.169 --> 00:26:23.356
I'll talk to Yoon Bok.

358
00:26:23.356 --> 00:26:26.335
And I'd like to speak to you, too.
Just for a moment.

359
00:26:29.823 --> 00:26:31.553
Do I make you feel uncomfortable?

360
00:26:33.089 --> 00:26:34.945
I'll sleep outside this house, then.

361
00:26:34.945 --> 00:26:37.010
I'm more used to sleeping
at the hospital, anyway.

362
00:26:37.010 --> 00:26:38.259
Doctor.

363
00:26:39.262 --> 00:26:40.842
Right now, I...

364
00:26:42.255 --> 00:26:45.172
want to go where nobody knows us.

365
00:26:46.025 --> 00:26:48.239
I would like it if there
was a lot for me to do.

366
00:26:48.239 --> 00:26:51.746
I would like it if
I were very, very busy.

367
00:26:54.231 --> 00:26:56.340
I'm very worried about Yoon Bok.

368
00:26:56.900 --> 00:26:59.598
That she'll know that I'm not
my normal self right now.

369
00:26:59.598 --> 00:27:02.571
And that she'll think that
I'm angry because of her.

370
00:27:04.622 --> 00:27:07.176
I want to hurry
and show her my normal self.

371
00:27:07.176 --> 00:27:09.042
Yoon Bok is okay.

372
00:27:09.042 --> 00:27:10.767
She's completely fine.

373
00:27:10.767 --> 00:27:12.021
No.

374
00:27:12.021 --> 00:27:14.284
Yoon Bok conceals her true feelings.

375
00:27:15.448 --> 00:27:17.936
<i>She'll say that she wasn't hit
even when she was hit</i>

376
00:27:17.936 --> 00:27:20.717
<i>and lies, saying that she's not
in pain when she actually is.</i>

377
00:27:20.717 --> 00:27:22.958
The one being like that
right now is you, Ms. Soo Jin.

378
00:27:24.148 --> 00:27:28.931
Right now, your mental state is the same
as if you'd been in a car accident.

379
00:27:28.931 --> 00:27:31.330
Your bones are broken
and you're bleeding profusely

380
00:27:31.330 --> 00:27:33.117
and yet you're insisting
that you can walk.

381
00:27:33.117 --> 00:27:35.278
You feel like you can walk
right now, don't you?

382
00:27:35.278 --> 00:27:37.997
But you'll only be able to take
a few steps before you fall down.

383
00:27:37.997 --> 00:27:39.423
Get some rest. Please.

384
00:27:39.423 --> 00:27:40.640
No.

385
00:27:41.236 --> 00:27:43.606
I'm not that badly injured.

386
00:27:44.586 --> 00:27:48.067
I abandoned that woman every day
in my heart, anyway.

387
00:27:49.167 --> 00:27:51.692
It's just that I abandoned her
in real life today, is all.

388
00:27:52.496 --> 00:27:54.550
You said that I wouldn't be
able to walk, right?

389
00:27:54.550 --> 00:27:55.902
You know, I...

390
00:27:55.902 --> 00:27:59.200
can get up tomorrow
and do the exact same thing again.

391
00:28:00.111 --> 00:28:02.011
It really doesn't phase me one bit.

392
00:28:09.873 --> 00:28:13.827
Apparently, she went to study abroad
in Iceland before Hye Na went missing.

393
00:28:13.827 --> 00:28:15.486
Iceland?

394
00:28:15.486 --> 00:28:17.712
<i>Yeah. Isn't that a relief?</i>

395
00:28:21.767 --> 00:28:24.063
The prepaid phone that you see here

396
00:28:24.063 --> 00:28:27.307
can be transferred to
up to four people.

397
00:28:33.645 --> 00:28:37.348
There were three kids in our class
who had cell phones.

398
00:28:37.940 --> 00:28:40.255
But they were the type that
they had to wear, right here.

399
00:28:40.255 --> 00:28:43.592
So the only one who has
an actual cell phone

400
00:28:43.592 --> 00:28:45.310
is me!

401
00:28:46.656 --> 00:28:48.755
I wish I could show everyone.

402
00:28:48.755 --> 00:28:50.413
I wonder what they'd say.

403
00:28:53.009 --> 00:28:55.512
There's something I need to
tell you, Yoon Bok.

404
00:28:56.032 --> 00:28:57.640
Look at Mommy.

405
00:28:59.034 --> 00:29:00.981
Starting from today

406
00:29:00.981 --> 00:29:03.201
we won't be living
at the barber shop.

407
00:29:06.155 --> 00:29:08.162
You're not going to ask me
the reason why?

408
00:29:09.047 --> 00:29:10.960
Is it because of me?

409
00:29:10.960 --> 00:29:12.275
No.

410
00:29:14.433 --> 00:29:18.167
I know that you and that lady
got along well with each other.

411
00:29:19.292 --> 00:29:22.304
That was so nice to see,
and I was so thankful for that.

412
00:29:23.919 --> 00:29:26.924
But Mommy and Barber Shop Lady
ended up fighting a little.

413
00:29:28.368 --> 00:29:32.675
You know that even adults can
fight with one another, right?

414
00:29:40.667 --> 00:29:43.593
Can I call Granny Finger?

415
00:29:45.871 --> 00:29:47.962
I told you this before

416
00:29:47.962 --> 00:29:50.864
but you can only call the number
saved on that phone, which is mine.

417
00:29:50.864 --> 00:29:54.782
You can't call or pick up calls
from other people.

418
00:29:54.782 --> 00:29:56.050
Okay?

419
00:29:57.142 --> 00:29:59.919
Let's stay at a hotel for tonight

420
00:29:59.919 --> 00:30:02.733
and then start looking for a place
to stay at, starting tomorrow.

421
00:30:03.969 --> 00:30:07.732
I won't leave you alone
and go off somewhere anymore.

422
00:30:07.732 --> 00:30:09.809
It's okay even if you leave me
alone and go somewhere.

423
00:30:09.809 --> 00:30:12.054
I have a cell phone now, after all!

424
00:30:12.834 --> 00:30:14.089
At any rate

425
00:30:14.089 --> 00:30:16.601
I'll come back
before dinnertime now.

426
00:30:21.799 --> 00:30:25.223
If you pull the string on this,
it turns into bibimbap.

427
00:30:25.223 --> 00:30:26.856
And I have black bean noodles, too!

428
00:30:26.856 --> 00:30:28.641
I can eat by myself.

429
00:30:30.013 --> 00:30:31.618
All right, thanks.

430
00:30:32.750 --> 00:30:37.604
I'm going to go to the cafe up front
for a bit since I have to meet someone.

431
00:30:41.997 --> 00:30:45.342
Right now, it's 2:54.

432
00:30:45.342 --> 00:30:48.622
I'll be back around
3:20 or 3:30.

433
00:30:48.622 --> 00:30:51.339
Can you wait for me by yourself
until then and play on the swings?

434
00:30:51.339 --> 00:30:52.516
All right.

435
00:31:01.988 --> 00:31:05.140
May I ask you who this is?

436
00:31:12.273 --> 00:31:13.842
She looks like you.

437
00:31:22.133 --> 00:31:25.141
There's still a lot of time until 3:20.

438
00:31:34.239 --> 00:31:35.741
<i>Soo Jin.</i>

439
00:31:35.741 --> 00:31:38.499
I know that you're smart.

440
00:31:39.070 --> 00:31:41.103
And I know that
if you wanted to disappear

441
00:31:41.103 --> 00:31:44.659
you would've definitely
been able to do so by now.

442
00:31:44.659 --> 00:31:46.938
Somewhere I wouldn't have
been able to find you.

443
00:31:46.938 --> 00:31:48.218
Right?

444
00:31:50.741 --> 00:31:51.972
But...

445
00:31:52.482 --> 00:31:55.144
you always came back.

446
00:31:57.142 --> 00:31:59.189
You have to come back on time
this time, okay?

447
00:31:59.787 --> 00:32:02.297
When your issue gets resolved,
come straight back.

448
00:32:02.806 --> 00:32:04.856
If you don't come back
on time this time around...

449
00:32:04.856 --> 00:32:07.022
I'll get really angry.

450
00:32:08.655 --> 00:32:10.820
You understand what
I'm saying, right?

451
00:32:16.307 --> 00:32:18.377
All right, Mister.

452
00:32:20.883 --> 00:32:24.202
So please, take good care of Mom
so that she doesn't pass away.

453
00:32:25.692 --> 00:32:27.699
It's not like your mom
ever listens to me.

454
00:32:33.941 --> 00:32:35.955
Granny!

455
00:32:39.979 --> 00:32:44.979
<font color="#fcc89b">[DramaFever Ver] tvN E06 Mother</font>
