00:35:58.099 --> 00:36:00.425
Yes, hello.
This is the insurance company, right?

505
00:36:01.168 --> 00:36:05.679
This is Jongro-gu, Pyeongchang-dong,
Pyeongchangmunwha-ro.

506
00:36:06.460 --> 00:36:08.204
Which street is this?

507
00:36:09.735 --> 00:36:12.132
- 24th street.
- Oh, 24th street.

508
00:36:12.132 --> 00:36:14.501
Yes, Pyeongchangmunwha-ro, 24th street.

509
00:36:14.501 --> 00:36:16.827
There was a collision. Yes.

510
00:36:18.278 --> 00:36:19.838
Thanks.

511
00:36:19.838 --> 00:36:21.253
You're so smart.

512
00:36:21.253 --> 00:36:22.400
Where do you live?

513
00:36:22.400 --> 00:36:24.083
Um...

514
00:36:24.684 --> 00:36:26.371
Do you live nearby?

515
00:36:27.432 --> 00:36:29.065
The barber shop.

516
00:36:29.065 --> 00:36:31.827
Oh, you mean Samhwa Barber Shop?

517
00:36:31.827 --> 00:36:33.543
You're their child, I see.

518
00:36:33.543 --> 00:36:35.077
No, that's not it.

519
00:36:35.077 --> 00:36:36.811
We're just living there for a bit.

520
00:36:36.811 --> 00:36:38.112
Oh, really?

521
00:36:38.112 --> 00:36:39.693
What's your name?

522
00:36:39.693 --> 00:36:42.824
I'm so thankful, so I want
to send you something.

523
00:36:42.824 --> 00:36:44.228
Um...

524
00:36:52.356 --> 00:36:54.117
Yoon Bok!

525
00:36:54.911 --> 00:36:56.878
Mom!

526
00:36:57.938 --> 00:36:59.530
Big Sis!

527
00:37:16.384 --> 00:37:18.007
Come here, Yoon Bok.

528
00:37:35.378 --> 00:37:37.436
Her name is...

529
00:37:37.436 --> 00:37:39.132
Yoon Bok?

530
00:37:40.512 --> 00:37:42.514
I'm sorry, Hyun Jin...

531
00:37:46.693 --> 00:37:50.804
but can't you keep it a secret
that you met me and Yoon Bok?

532
00:37:51.891 --> 00:37:53.034
Big Sis.

533
00:37:53.034 --> 00:37:57.284
Mom raised three daughters
without a father.

534
00:37:57.284 --> 00:38:01.422
There's nobody else who'd
understand you better than Mom.

535
00:38:01.422 --> 00:38:03.054
It's because I'm running out of time.

536
00:38:03.054 --> 00:38:04.539
We have to leave soon.

537
00:38:04.539 --> 00:38:06.909
As quietly and quickly as possible.

538
00:38:07.690 --> 00:38:09.326
I'll explain things later.

539
00:38:09.326 --> 00:38:12.746
There's nobody who's more
short on time right now than Mom.

540
00:38:13.360 --> 00:38:17.519
Mom may end up passing away
without ever even knowing

541
00:38:17.519 --> 00:38:19.706
that you have a daughter.

542
00:38:21.253 --> 00:38:23.813
You don't know how much
Mom loves kids, do you?

543
00:38:23.813 --> 00:38:27.025
Whenever she sees kids,
her eyes start sparkling.

544
00:38:27.025 --> 00:38:30.784
She's the type to cancel on a live show
just for Tae Mi and Tae Hoon.

545
00:38:31.494 --> 00:38:33.735
If Mom sees Yoon Bok

546
00:38:33.735 --> 00:38:35.500
she'll feel more encouraged to live on.

547
00:38:36.358 --> 00:38:37.838
It's most important...

548
00:38:38.733 --> 00:38:41.376
to maintain her will to
survive, don't you think?

549
00:38:42.079 --> 00:38:43.554
I'm sorry, Hyun Jin.

550
00:38:44.173 --> 00:38:45.858
But Mom wouldn't understand.

551
00:38:45.858 --> 00:38:48.038
Neither would you or Yi Jin.

552
00:38:48.038 --> 00:38:50.804
Because even I can't understand
the situation I'm in right now.

553
00:38:50.804 --> 00:38:52.987
The only thing that I know for sure

554
00:38:52.987 --> 00:38:55.451
is that I must take that child

555
00:38:55.451 --> 00:38:58.043
and go far, far away from here.

556
00:39:00.664 --> 00:39:02.266
All right.

557
00:39:03.534 --> 00:39:07.244
I do understand how you must feel.

558
00:39:07.931 --> 00:39:11.244
But, I'm a reporter.

559
00:39:11.244 --> 00:39:14.855
I'm just naturally bad at saying
I haven't seen something that I've seen.

560
00:39:15.824 --> 00:39:18.699
You've asked me to do
something that's too difficult.

561
00:39:43.090 --> 00:39:45.884
Have we been exposed now?

562
00:39:47.711 --> 00:39:49.268
No, we're okay.

563
00:39:49.268 --> 00:39:50.686
Don't worry about it.

564
00:39:50.686 --> 00:39:52.768
I'm sorry.

565
00:39:52.768 --> 00:39:55.061
You didn't do anything wrong.

566
00:39:55.061 --> 00:39:56.847
Everything will be fine.

567
00:39:56.847 --> 00:39:59.570
I have to go somewhere.

568
00:40:00.987 --> 00:40:04.427
And I'll be back by 4:30.

569
00:40:04.427 --> 00:40:06.168
Stay here and eat.

570
00:40:06.168 --> 00:40:07.925
Let's go eat dinner
together after I get back.

571
00:40:07.925 --> 00:40:10.157
I'll leave my bag and my coffee here

572
00:40:10.157 --> 00:40:13.605
so if someone asks, tell them
that I went to the bathroom.

573
00:40:13.605 --> 00:40:16.163
And if anything happens, call me.

574
00:40:16.891 --> 00:40:18.331
Can you do that?

575
00:40:18.331 --> 00:40:21.485
All right. Have a good time
in the bathroom.

576
00:40:25.001 --> 00:40:26.590
I'm home.

577
00:40:26.590 --> 00:40:28.083
Oh, hey.

578
00:40:28.083 --> 00:40:29.202
Oh, you're back?

579
00:40:29.202 --> 00:40:30.965
Eat this.

580
00:40:30.965 --> 00:40:32.896
- Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!
- Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

581
00:40:32.896 --> 00:40:34.666
Yum, that's good.

582
00:40:34.666 --> 00:40:37.306
Mom ordered beef from Hoengseong.

583
00:40:37.306 --> 00:40:39.367
She wants to make sure she's
well-fed before she goes abroad.

584
00:40:39.367 --> 00:40:41.563
They don't have braised short ribs
abroad, after all.

585
00:40:48.983 --> 00:40:50.443
I'm here.

586
00:40:50.443 --> 00:40:52.697
Oh, you're here?
Your eldest aunt is here.

587
00:40:52.697 --> 00:40:54.804
- Hello.
- Hello.

588
00:40:54.804 --> 00:40:55.840
Hey.

589
00:40:55.840 --> 00:40:57.632
You came earlier than expected.

590
00:40:57.632 --> 00:40:59.400
It needs to cook a bit longer.

591
00:41:05.000 --> 00:41:06.568
It's delicious.

592
00:41:15.914 --> 00:41:18.224
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

593
00:41:18.224 --> 00:41:21.898
Don't you think she's suddenly
being way too nice to you?

594
00:41:21.898 --> 00:41:24.967
I feel like she's putting on airs
as a future chairwoman.

595
00:41:24.967 --> 00:41:26.471
What do you mean by that?

596
00:41:26.471 --> 00:41:28.945
You don't know since you
left early yesterday

597
00:41:28.945 --> 00:41:31.625
but Yi Ji will become a chairwoman.

598
00:41:31.625 --> 00:41:34.726
Ask our attorney when you next see him.

599
00:41:35.918 --> 00:41:37.016
Mom.

600
00:41:37.016 --> 00:41:39.666
I don't think I'll be able to
eat dinner with you all today.

601
00:41:39.666 --> 00:41:40.936
Why not?

602
00:41:58.019 --> 00:42:02.217
Mom said that she'd be here at 4:30.

603
00:42:02.217 --> 00:42:05.795
And it's 4:05 right now.

604
00:42:05.795 --> 00:42:08.391
So, the amount of time there is
left until she gets back is...

605
00:42:09.347 --> 00:42:10.733
um...

606
00:42:15.204 --> 00:42:17.521
One, two minutes...

607
00:42:17.521 --> 00:42:21.153
three, four, five...

608
00:42:21.153 --> 00:42:22.431
six...

609
00:42:22.914 --> 00:42:26.210
Something urgent came up,
so I have to go.

610
00:42:26.210 --> 00:42:27.597
And...

611
00:42:28.226 --> 00:42:30.387
as for the time that
we meet each other

612
00:42:30.387 --> 00:42:33.204
- let's meet earlier from now on...
- Soo Jin.

613
00:42:33.204 --> 00:42:35.806
You have to tell me
what the urgent matter is.

614
00:42:35.806 --> 00:42:40.510
Everyone got together at this time
today so we could have dinner with you.

615
00:42:40.510 --> 00:42:43.967
So if you can't tell us why
you can't stay

616
00:42:43.967 --> 00:42:47.072
that would be too rude of you.

617
00:42:47.711 --> 00:42:50.599
Wait, you're going to leave
without eating?

618
00:42:51.465 --> 00:42:52.485
I'm sorry.

619
00:42:52.485 --> 00:42:54.617
What are you saying?
Just have a bite, at least.

620
00:42:54.617 --> 00:42:56.795
It's not like it'll take you
several hours to eat.

621
00:42:56.795 --> 00:42:59.559
Yeah, and tell us what this
"urgent matter" is.

622
00:43:14.452 --> 00:43:16.010
Doctor Jung?

623
00:43:16.010 --> 00:43:17.523
What is it?

624
00:43:19.121 --> 00:43:21.349
Wait, you're on your way
to our place right now?

625
00:43:23.686 --> 00:43:26.340
What? You want to know if it's
okay if you take Soo Jin?

626
00:43:27.257 --> 00:43:28.844
When?

627
00:43:29.547 --> 00:43:31.257
Where are you going?

628
00:43:31.952 --> 00:43:33.688
You're going on a drive

629
00:43:33.688 --> 00:43:35.998
and then going to eat dinner afterward?

630
00:43:40.690 --> 00:43:43.804
So you did have an urgent matter
that you couldn't tell me about.

631
00:43:44.324 --> 00:43:45.431
Eat before you go.

632
00:43:45.431 --> 00:43:48.163
Doctor Jung can eat first, too.
I've made more than enough.

633
00:43:48.163 --> 00:43:49.211
Hey.

634
00:43:49.211 --> 00:43:52.373
What's more important right now?
Short ribs or a man?

635
00:43:53.030 --> 00:43:55.326
You did even worse things
when you were younger.

636
00:43:56.699 --> 00:43:58.434
Hurry and go.

637
00:44:04.492 --> 00:44:05.753
Soo Jin.

638
00:44:05.753 --> 00:44:07.139
Get in.

639
00:44:19.726 --> 00:44:21.492
<i>Oh, goodness me.</i>

640
00:44:21.492 --> 00:44:23.556
Look at her,
just getting in like it's nothing.

641
00:44:23.556 --> 00:44:25.896
They don't seem to have
an ordinary relationship.

642
00:44:28.844 --> 00:44:30.025
I'm sorry.

643
00:44:30.025 --> 00:44:31.385
I surprised you, didn't I?

644
00:44:32.050 --> 00:44:33.481
Yes, I was surprised.

645
00:44:33.481 --> 00:44:36.679
There's a place I really
need to go with you right now.

646
00:44:36.679 --> 00:44:38.809
But there was no way for me
to contact you sooner.

647
00:44:38.809 --> 00:44:40.882
And we can't be late.

648
00:44:40.882 --> 00:44:42.166
Where are we going?

649
00:44:42.166 --> 00:44:43.628
Um...

650
00:44:43.628 --> 00:44:45.985
it's somewhere I go often in
the evening, on weekends.

651
00:44:45.985 --> 00:44:48.626
And sometimes I spend
the night there, too.

652
00:44:50.188 --> 00:44:51.802
Where's Yoon Bok?

653
00:44:53.623 --> 00:44:56.472
What kind of relationship do
Doctor Jung and Big Sis have?

654
00:44:56.472 --> 00:44:58.809
I'm not really sure.

655
00:44:58.809 --> 00:45:01.972
They have met up three times
just this week, though.

656
00:45:01.972 --> 00:45:03.186
What?

657
00:45:03.659 --> 00:45:05.282
You really are amazing, Mom.

658
00:45:05.282 --> 00:45:07.496
You go out of your way to
find your daughter a husband

659
00:45:07.496 --> 00:45:09.322
even when you're so ill.

660
00:45:09.322 --> 00:45:11.112
Thanks to that,
you managed to get married.

661
00:45:11.112 --> 00:45:12.739
Yeah, but it's not a happy marriage.

662
00:45:13.847 --> 00:45:15.934
There's no such thing
as a happy marriage.

663
00:45:15.934 --> 00:45:18.907
It's good enough that you
gave birth to such cute pups.

664
00:45:18.907 --> 00:45:21.280
- They don't suit each other.
- What are you talking about?

665
00:45:21.280 --> 00:45:23.293
How old is Doctor Jung, again?

666
00:45:23.293 --> 00:45:25.626
- Isn't he younger?
- What are you saying?

667
00:45:25.626 --> 00:45:28.157
Soo Jin definitely looks
younger than him.

668
00:45:28.157 --> 00:45:31.322
It's a bit strange that a doctor
his age is still not married, too.

669
00:45:31.322 --> 00:45:34.561
If he were half decent, some woman
would've snatched him away by now.

670
00:45:35.947 --> 00:45:38.213
Maybe Doctor Jung has issues?

671
00:45:39.039 --> 00:45:40.556
We managed to get here just in time.

672
00:45:40.556 --> 00:45:43.282
We have to go in before the sun sets
and grab ourselves a spot.

673
00:45:43.282 --> 00:45:45.735
The evening migration will start soon.

674
00:45:45.735 --> 00:45:50.092
When that's over, the oriental
greenfinches will be the first to come.

675
00:45:50.092 --> 00:45:53.621
Then, the meadow buntings.
And then the woodpeckers.

676
00:45:54.275 --> 00:45:56.237
And when it gets quiet...

677
00:45:56.237 --> 00:45:57.931
take a good look.

678
00:45:57.931 --> 00:46:00.137
The solitary snipes might even come out.

679
00:46:01.670 --> 00:46:03.434
A solitary snipe?

680
00:46:04.318 --> 00:46:08.164
They say that it takes three generations'
worth of effort to see a solitary snipe

681
00:46:08.164 --> 00:46:11.327
but I've seen them here for three years
straight now, right around this time.

682
00:46:11.327 --> 00:46:14.219
There's a valley if we walk
a bit more up from here.

683
00:46:14.219 --> 00:46:16.135
And there's a flat boulder near there.

684
00:46:16.135 --> 00:46:17.849
Sit right there, and don't move.

685
00:46:17.849 --> 00:46:20.597
The birds start moving around 30 minutes
before the sun sets.

686
00:46:22.672 --> 00:46:24.949
Hm, you should get going now.

687
00:46:26.074 --> 00:46:27.559
You want me to go alone?

688
00:46:27.559 --> 00:46:29.338
Just stay there for
30 minutes and come back.

689
00:46:29.338 --> 00:46:32.505
All by yourself, in a place
where nobody can find you.

690
00:46:35.032 --> 00:46:36.452
Yoon Bok.

691
00:46:36.452 --> 00:46:39.657
You're okay with being with me
while your mom goes there, right?

692
00:46:40.672 --> 00:46:42.492
Have fun, Mom.

693
00:47:19.322 --> 00:47:24.159
<i>There was a baby rabbit
that wanted to run away.</i>

694
00:47:25.112 --> 00:47:28.289
<i>"I'm going to run away, Mom."</i>

695
00:47:29.559 --> 00:47:33.391
<i>"I'll chase after you
if you run away."</i>

696
00:47:34.347 --> 00:47:37.168
<i>"Because you are my adorable child."</i>

697
00:47:37.985 --> 00:47:40.019
"If you follow me, Mom"

698
00:47:40.019 --> 00:47:43.320
"I'll go to the riverside
and become a fish."

699
00:47:43.320 --> 00:47:46.512
"And I'll swim away."

700
00:47:46.512 --> 00:47:49.889
"If you go to the riverside
and become a fish"

701
00:47:49.889 --> 00:47:52.327
"I'll become a fisherman."

702
00:47:52.327 --> 00:47:54.896
"Then, I'll catch you."

703
00:48:06.429 --> 00:48:09.164
<i>"If you become
a fisherman, Mom"</i>

704
00:48:09.164 --> 00:48:12.335
<i>"I'll go to a mountain that is
much higher than the one you're at"</i>

705
00:48:12.335 --> 00:48:14.552
<i>"and become a rock."</i>

706
00:48:16.757 --> 00:48:20.795
<i>I'm going to give
everything to this child.</i>

707
00:48:20.795 --> 00:48:23.251
<i>I will give many,
many things to this child.</i>

708
00:48:23.876 --> 00:48:25.146
<i>Until...</i>

709
00:48:25.146 --> 00:48:27.610
<i>the child forgets about all
of her old scars completely.</i>

710
00:48:28.693 --> 00:48:31.251
<i>That is quite important to me.</i>

711
00:48:31.251 --> 00:48:32.353
<i>Because...</i>

712
00:48:32.353 --> 00:48:34.768
<i>that is a matter that
involves my very soul.</i>

713
00:48:36.474 --> 00:48:40.586
"If you go to a high mountaintop
and become a rock"

714
00:48:40.586 --> 00:48:43.282
"I will become a hiker."

715
00:48:43.282 --> 00:48:46.760
"Then, I will climb up
to where you are."

716
00:48:47.398 --> 00:48:48.780
<i>No.</i>

717
00:48:48.780 --> 00:48:51.829
<i>I don't need a lot of things.</i>

718
00:48:52.297 --> 00:48:54.862
<i>Getting things like that makes me think</i>

719
00:48:54.862 --> 00:48:57.184
<i>that the mother who gave birth to me</i>

720
00:48:57.184 --> 00:49:00.420
<i>may have abandoned me because
she couldn't give me these things.</i>

721
00:49:00.420 --> 00:49:03.481
<i>But I can live without
these sorts of things.</i>

722
00:49:37.856 --> 00:49:39.838
<i>I'm sure that the person
who abandoned Soo Jin</i>

723
00:49:39.838 --> 00:49:41.985
<i>had her own reasons for doing so.</i>

724
00:49:48.030 --> 00:49:51.873
<i>But when I think about
how my child was abandoned</i>

725
00:49:51.873 --> 00:49:55.204
<i>my desire to be understanding of her
circumstances completely vanishes.</i>

726
00:49:56.233 --> 00:49:59.079
<i>The child had wounds all over her body</i>

727
00:49:59.079 --> 00:50:01.108
<i>and she was tied down with a lock</i>

728
00:50:01.108 --> 00:50:03.472
<i>so that she couldn't escape.</i>

729
00:50:03.472 --> 00:50:06.639
<i>The only acceptable excuse to me</i>

730
00:50:06.639 --> 00:50:08.150
<i>that I could be understanding of...</i>

731
00:50:08.853 --> 00:50:10.717
<i>is that she died.</i>

732
00:50:12.164 --> 00:50:13.739
<i>If that were the case...</i>

733
00:50:14.498 --> 00:50:19.760
<i>I could say, "Oh, so that's why she
could no longer raise the child."</i>

734
00:50:19.760 --> 00:50:22.885
<i>and understand why
she did what she did.</i>

735
00:50:31.909 --> 00:50:35.702
<i>"I'll become a bird and fly
far, far away."</i>

736
00:50:35.702 --> 00:50:38.498
<i>If this goes on TV</i>

737
00:50:38.498 --> 00:50:41.175
<i>will everyone be able to see me?</i>

738
00:50:41.175 --> 00:50:44.213
<i>Everyone in this country
will be able to see you.</i>

739
00:50:44.213 --> 00:50:47.628
<i>Is there anyone that
you hope will see you?</i>

740
00:50:49.554 --> 00:50:52.795
<i>What do you want them
to see about you, exactly?</i>

741
00:50:55.706 --> 00:50:58.505
<i>That I'm doing well.</i>

742
00:51:00.938 --> 00:51:04.806
<i>"If you become a bird
and fly far, far away"</i>

743
00:51:04.806 --> 00:51:07.054
<i>"I will become a tree"</i>

744
00:51:07.054 --> 00:51:09.628
<i>"and wait for you here."</i>

745
00:51:10.481 --> 00:51:12.286
<i>"Forever."</i>

746
00:51:29.938 --> 00:51:32.297
<i>I'm doing well.</i>

747
00:51:52.222 --> 00:51:53.972
Are you taking customers?

748
00:51:55.050 --> 00:51:57.590
Of course. Come on in.

749
00:52:00.155 --> 00:52:03.108
What are their names?

750
00:52:04.626 --> 00:52:08.347
One of them is named Soo,
and the other one is named Jin.

751
00:52:08.347 --> 00:52:10.635
Oh, Soo and Jin.

752
00:52:14.396 --> 00:52:15.543
Oh, goodness.

753
00:52:15.543 --> 00:52:17.981
I have to feed them.

754
00:52:22.420 --> 00:52:23.844
Oh no!

755
00:52:23.844 --> 00:52:25.800
The birds need to be fed.

756
00:52:25.800 --> 00:52:26.920
Huh?

757
00:52:27.572 --> 00:52:30.336
I forgot to return the key
for the bird cage to her.

758
00:52:31.639 --> 00:52:33.920
Even though I was the one
who was in charge of the birds.

759
00:52:33.920 --> 00:52:35.737
Yoon Bok!

760
00:52:35.737 --> 00:52:37.456
Mom!

761
00:52:42.065 --> 00:52:44.190
Did you have a good time, Mom?

762
00:52:45.539 --> 00:52:47.173
Did you have a good time?

763
00:52:53.599 --> 00:52:55.945
Big Sis has a kid?

764
00:52:55.945 --> 00:53:00.021
She wants me to keep it
a secret from Mom.

765
00:53:00.795 --> 00:53:02.929
But I don't think I should.

766
00:53:03.179 --> 00:53:05.483
Big Sis has a kid?

767
00:53:05.978 --> 00:53:09.704
She wants me to keep it
a secret from Mom.

768
00:53:10.434 --> 00:53:12.896
But I don't think I should.

769
00:53:12.896 --> 00:53:14.711
Why not?

770
00:53:15.568 --> 00:53:18.918
Mom will be so happy
if she sees that child.

771
00:53:19.438 --> 00:53:23.005
At this rate, she'll pass away without
knowing that Big Sis has a daughter.

772
00:53:23.005 --> 00:53:26.713
Why do you think that we were unaware of
the fact that she had a kid up until now?

773
00:53:27.356 --> 00:53:31.456
If she had a proper child, then we
would've known about her by now.

774
00:53:31.456 --> 00:53:34.291
What if Big Sis is some
married guy's side chick?

775
00:53:34.291 --> 00:53:37.152
You think that Mom will be happy to
find out that she's a home wrecker

776
00:53:37.152 --> 00:53:40.103
and is on the run with a kid, when
she raised Big Sis with so much care?

777
00:53:40.811 --> 00:53:44.304
Even the strongest parents
will crumble if they find out

778
00:53:44.304 --> 00:53:46.534
that their daughter did
something horrific.

779
00:53:46.534 --> 00:53:49.748
Yet, you think Mom will be
happy, despite this situation?

780
00:53:50.978 --> 00:53:52.333
What do I do?

781
00:53:52.333 --> 00:53:54.974
What do you mean?
Keep quiet about it, of course.

782
00:53:54.974 --> 00:53:57.210
We have to keep it hidden,
and send them off well.

783
00:53:59.666 --> 00:54:02.967
Wow, I really can't believe Soo Jin.

784
00:54:02.967 --> 00:54:05.184
She was talking as if she had
no intention of ever having kids

785
00:54:05.184 --> 00:54:07.293
when we were discussing
the inheritance yesterday!

786
00:54:15.099 --> 00:54:17.550
Here I come!

787
00:54:20.010 --> 00:54:23.552
Why are Mom and Auntie
talking over there, when it's cold?

788
00:54:23.552 --> 00:54:26.074
Mom and Auntie are talking?

789
00:54:26.074 --> 00:54:28.577
Those two usually
don't talk to each other.

790
00:54:30.237 --> 00:54:34.306
<i>We usually go to that spot when
we're discussing secret matters.</i>

791
00:54:39.157 --> 00:54:40.210
Honey.

792
00:54:40.210 --> 00:54:42.282
Do you know where Iceland is?

793
00:54:44.014 --> 00:54:45.619
It's at the edge of the earth.

794
00:54:48.983 --> 00:54:51.376
I think it'll be fine, honestly.

795
00:54:51.376 --> 00:54:53.813
Even if that woman
Kang Soo Jin took Hye Na

796
00:54:53.813 --> 00:54:56.206
if the two of them are in
Iceland, well, then...

797
00:54:58.393 --> 00:55:00.597
Why did they say that she
went to Iceland, again?

798
00:55:01.726 --> 00:55:03.661
To study.

799
00:55:03.661 --> 00:55:05.786
What did she say that
she was studying, again?

800
00:55:06.820 --> 00:55:07.976
Birds?

801
00:55:23.869 --> 00:55:25.074
Honey.

802
00:55:26.373 --> 00:55:28.344
Let's have a nice life now.

803
00:55:30.791 --> 00:55:33.583
It's just the two of us now.

804
00:55:44.101 --> 00:55:46.987
What are you plotting with Soo Jin?

805
00:55:46.987 --> 00:55:48.688
She'll be leaving soon.

806
00:55:48.688 --> 00:55:50.164
That's all I can tell you.

807
00:55:50.164 --> 00:55:51.813
When is she leaving?

808
00:55:51.813 --> 00:55:54.030
In about two weeks or so.

809
00:55:54.030 --> 00:55:58.155
If she wants to leave, she should hurry.
Why is she here for another two weeks?

810
00:55:58.753 --> 00:56:00.789
Is there a problem?

811
00:56:01.335 --> 00:56:03.900
I'll tell you later.

812
00:56:04.829 --> 00:56:07.797
She's a home wrecker,
and a single mom, to boot?

813
00:56:07.797 --> 00:56:11.541
Wow, Soo Jin really is hopeless.
I didn't think she was like that.

814
00:56:13.481 --> 00:56:15.820
No, that's not what happened.

815
00:56:26.157 --> 00:56:27.481
Yes, Madam?

816
00:56:36.579 --> 00:56:39.943
Can't we stop by the barber shop, Mom?

817
00:56:39.943 --> 00:56:41.045
Why?

818
00:56:41.045 --> 00:56:44.135
I took the key for
the bird cage by accident.

819
00:56:44.135 --> 00:56:46.648
Granny won't be able to feed them.

820
00:57:23.719 --> 00:57:25.702
I'm sorry, Mom.

821
00:57:26.599 --> 00:57:27.713
All right.

822
00:57:27.713 --> 00:57:29.599
Tell me your side of the story now.

823
00:57:31.434 --> 00:57:36.887
I kept thinking that I should
have told you about this.

824
00:57:38.231 --> 00:57:41.871
But I'm sure that Soo Jin
has her own reasons.

825
00:57:43.878 --> 00:57:44.990
<i>Hey.</i>

826
00:57:48.030 --> 00:57:49.228
Yes.

827
00:57:49.789 --> 00:57:52.487
I'm sure that Soo Jin
has her own reasons.

828
00:57:52.487 --> 00:57:54.773
But that's Soo Jin's problem.

829
00:57:54.773 --> 00:57:57.824
When were you planning
to tell me about this, then?

830
00:57:59.972 --> 00:58:02.175
First, Soo Jin...

831
00:58:03.164 --> 00:58:06.362
would have to have made all the
preparations to move with the child...

832
00:58:13.130 --> 00:58:14.592
So...

833
00:58:15.635 --> 00:58:19.083
Soo Jin has a child?

834
00:58:52.981 --> 00:58:54.514
Those little...

835
00:59:02.367 --> 00:59:04.231
Granny!

836
00:59:06.956 --> 00:59:08.947
Oh my word.

837
00:59:08.947 --> 00:59:10.735
Oh... my goodness.

838
00:59:15.231 --> 00:59:16.704
Goodness.

839
00:59:26.012 --> 00:59:28.315
You should feed them now, Granny.

840
00:59:28.315 --> 00:59:30.521
I'm sure that they must have been hungry.

841
00:59:32.056 --> 00:59:35.313
But is your cold
all better now, Granny?

842
00:59:46.943 --> 00:59:48.541
Thank you for everything.

843
00:59:49.900 --> 00:59:51.534
Let's go again sometime.

844
00:59:51.534 --> 00:59:53.391
Can we?

845
00:59:54.478 --> 00:59:55.925
Let's go tomorrow.

846
00:59:57.088 --> 00:59:59.438
Because I have to go to work on Monday.

847
01:00:01.574 --> 01:00:03.007
Sure.

848
01:00:05.954 --> 01:00:08.400
Is it because of me that you're
not going in to say hello?

849
01:00:08.400 --> 01:00:09.842
No.

850
01:01:01.090 --> 01:01:02.527
Yoon Bok.

851
01:01:02.527 --> 01:01:03.884
Let's get going now.

852
01:01:03.884 --> 01:01:05.300
All right.

853
01:01:37.235 --> 01:01:39.661
Oh my goodness!

854
01:01:45.070 --> 01:01:47.711
Are you the woman
who abandoned my daughter?

855
01:02:01.137 --> 01:02:06.362
<i>[Call Me Mother / Mother]</i>

856
01:02:06.862 --> 01:02:07.862
Subtitles by DramaFever

857
01:02:20.809 --> 01:02:21.998
<i>Is she the kid?</i>

858
01:02:21.998 --> 01:02:23.244
<i>Why were you hiding her?</i>

859
01:02:23.244 --> 01:02:24.335
<i>Is there a problem?</i>

860
01:02:24.335 --> 01:02:25.961
<i>You're Kang Soo Jin's daughter?</i>

861
01:02:25.961 --> 01:02:28.092
<i>- Yes.
- I'm your grandma.</i>

862
01:02:28.092 --> 01:02:29.663
<i>Grandma.</i>

863
01:02:29.663 --> 01:02:32.480
<i>Could I see a photo of
Hye Na, by any chance?</i>

864
01:02:32.480 --> 01:02:35.601
<i>She seems to look similar
to a girl that I know, you see.</i>

865
01:02:35.601 --> 01:02:38.514
<i>What are the chances
that I'll still be alive</i>

866
01:02:38.514 --> 01:02:40.726
<i>to see a girl who is
seven years old now enter college?</i>

867
01:02:40.726 --> 01:02:42.815
<i>I remembered the memory
that I'd forgotten.</i>

868
01:02:42.815 --> 01:02:45.896
<i>The one where my mom, whom I'd
waited for for so long, tried to kill me.</i>

869
01:02:45.896 --> 01:02:47.403
<i>The woman from Samhwa Barber Shop...</i>

870
01:02:47.403 --> 01:02:50.507
<i>go put her somewhere far away
so that I will never see her again.</i>

